Method Detail

hierarchy

public static List<Class<?>> hierarchy(Class<?> klazz)
This method returns a complete list of all Classes in the hierarchy of the object sent in as the argument including itself and all the way up to and including Object.
e.g. for class hierarchy: 
     Object
       |
    Vehicle
    |     |
   Car  Motorcycle
Calling ClassHierarchyUtil.hierarchy(Car.class) will return [Car.class, Vehicle.class, Object.class] as a list

Parameters:
klazz - the class for which to get the class hierarchy list
Returns:
a list of classes that are in the hierarchy of the argument class from, and including, itself up to, and including, Object

createInstance

public static <T> T createInstance(String name)
                        throws ReflectionException
This method attempts to load the given class using ClassLoader.loadClass(String). Given that the class is found, it then creates an instance using createInstance(Class)

Type Parameters:
T - the type of the resulting class
Parameters:
name - the fully qualified name of the class to load
Returns:
an instance of the class for the given fully qualified domain name
Throws:
ReflectionException - if the class is not found or if an instance can not be created

createInstance

public static <T> T createInstance(Class<T> clazz)
                        throws ReflectionException
This method creates a new instance of the given class.
Class must have a no args constructor. The constructor can be below public access(e.g. private) but it must be present.

Type Parameters:
T - the class type
Parameters:
clazz - class of the object you want instantiated. e.g. User.class
Returns:
an instance of the given class
Throws:
ReflectionException - if an instance could not be created
